textRun.content: Ok so as you know I do not have a good relationship with my own biological mother. I however don’t have all bad memories of our time together before I had to make the decision to remove her from our lives. One of the memories that I do have is about us making kitchen sink cookies together. She was a bit of a health nut and thought that these protein packed cookies could be a healthy snack. I however didn’t think that they would be that good so I was hesitant. These are so good that I had to redo my thinking on healthy snacks from then on. I love you dearly.
* ¼ cup milk powder (⅓ cup instant)
** ¼ cup oil or melted butter
Mix all dry ingredients * in one bowl
Mix all wet ingredients ** in separate bowl
Combine the wet mixture into the dry mixture. If the dough is too dry add some milk or water until “drop cookie” consistency
